SIMPLE: elude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elude
<hw>E*lude"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Eluded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Eluding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>eludere</ets>,
<ets>elusum</ets>; <ets>e</ets> + <ets>ludere</ets> to play: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧luder</ets>. See <er>Ludicrous</er>.]</ety> <def>To avoid
slyly, by artifice, stratagem, or dexterity; to escape from in a covert
manner; to mock by an unexpected escape; to baffle; <as>as, to
<ex>elude</ex> an officer; to <ex>elude</ex> detection, inquiry, search,
comprehension; to <ex>elude</ex> the force of an argument or a
blow.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Me gentle Delia beckons from the plain,⟦br⟧
Then, hid in shades, <qex>eludes</qex> he eager swain.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The transition from fetichism to polytheism seems a gradual
process of which the stages <qex>elude</qex> close definition.</q>
<rj><qau>Tylor.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To evade; avoid; escape; shun; eschew; flee;
mock; baffle; frustrate; foil.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eludible</ent>⟦br⟧
